Extremely well-thought game, with a deceptively simple look. For such a basic wireframe world, it is easy to get sucked in & lose track of time as you struggle to pass levels. If you're going for record scores there is a LOT of repetition, trying to nail every jump at the precise moment needed. Might be too frustrating for some, but you can take it easier & just go for level completion instead. There are lots of side challenges to achieve, and a multiplayer version that puts you head-to-head with someone on the same device. Absolutely worth a try if you're a twitch gamer.

I love the wire frame design. It takes the game to a different dimension, with more effort into the game itself, and not on "cutesy" backgrounds. I also appreciate the first person POV. 
The game itself is never boring, easy to play, but hard as hell to master. I've spent hrs playing without realizing it.

title.label: Great style but not for everyone

content.label: Looks and sounds terrific, but this game is about learning how to execute precise reactions with split-moment timing. You wind up trying—and failing—the same things over and over and over again. Some will find the experience zen and engrossing. Others will loathe it all.
